<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%=title%>></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="ml-50 mr-50">
      <h1 class="text-center mt-5 mb-5 text-3xl"><%=title%></h1>
      <div class="my-5 border-t-1 border-b-1 border-blue-200 py-2">
        <p>Your name: <%=user.fullname%></p>
        <p>Your username: <%=user.username%></p>
      </div>
      <div class="my-5 border-t-1 border-b-1 border-blue-200 py-2">
        <p>Your membership status:</p>
        <p class="text-center underline mt-2 mb-2">
          <%=user.membership_status%>
        </p>
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <a
            href="/join/<%=user.id%>"
            class="mb-5 mt-5 px-10 py-1.5 bg-blue-400 text-white hover:bg-blue-300 hover:cursor-pointer"
            >Become a Member</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="border-1 border-gray-200 text-center">FAQs</h2>
        <p class="border-t-1 border-blue-200 mt-3">
          What is the difference between my name and username?
        </p>
        <p class="border-b-1 border-blue-200 pb-3 italic text-sm mt-2">
          - Your username is used only for logging in, while your name is
          displayed on posts and messages that you leave.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
